text:
\>the concept of the trinity therefore has to be sold to people in misty,vague, poetic language that doesn't ultimately make rational sense

&#x200B;

disagree. The concept of the trinity has been defined by the authorities of the faith in a clear, precise philosophical language. There is nothing "misty" or "vague" about it, except maybe if you ask the layman who isn't familiar with the actual teaching. Just because you can't draw a 100\_% accurate diagram of the transcendend Godhead doesn't mean it's illogical
